(45, '399da42a-5c50-431e-8601-7cb58c30e1e8', '06834f36-fee9-4f77-a7e1-cb1509514dc7', '2e20ac4187818', '<p id=\"isPasted\">More than 50,000 people have signed an online petition urging the Food and Drug Monitoring Agency (BPOM) to issue a label that warns consumers of the dangers of Bisphenol A (BPA), a chemical compound often found in galon, 19-liter plastic water containers.</p><p>The petitioner, the Health and Eco-Conscious Journalist Association (JPKL), believes no Indonesian authorities have made any moves to warn the public about potential health risks caused by the chemical substance.</p><p>Water containers commonly distributed in Indonesia are made from polycarbonate or hard plastic that often uses BPA in its production. BPA is also found in canned food linings.</p><p>Studies show that the compound, which theoretically acts like a hormone in the body, might raise <a href=\"https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2013/10/14/study-ties-chemical-possible-miscarriage-risk.html\">the&nbsp;risk&nbsp;of&nbsp;infertility,&nbsp;h</a>eart problems, cancer and other health problems. Infants and young children are at a higher risk as their system of eliminating harmful substances is still developing.</p><p>The&nbsp;JPKL&nbsp;demanded that&nbsp;the&nbsp;BPOM&nbsp;require&nbsp;producers to&nbsp;add&nbsp;the&nbsp;plastic&nbsp;recycling&nbsp;symbol&nbsp;number&nbsp;seven&nbsp;in&nbsp;any&nbsp;plastic packaging&nbsp;that&nbsp;contains&nbsp;BPA.</p><p>&ldquo;This is to protect the future of [children] and pregnant women, so they won&rsquo;t be exposed to the dangerous chemical compound,&rdquo; JPKL head Roro Daras wrote in the petition.</p><p>The&nbsp;JPKL&nbsp;demanded that&nbsp;the&nbsp;BPOM&nbsp;require&nbsp;producers to&nbsp;add&nbsp;the&nbsp;plastic&nbsp;recycling&nbsp;symbol&nbsp;number&nbsp;seven&nbsp;in&nbsp;any&nbsp;plastic packaging&nbsp;that&nbsp;contains&nbsp;BPA.</p><p>&nbsp;&ldquo;This is to protect the future of [children] and pregnant women, so they won&rsquo;t be exposed to the dangerous chemical compound,&rdquo; JPKL head Roro Daras wrote in the petition.</p><p>The&nbsp;Indonesian&nbsp;Food&nbsp;Testing&nbsp;Laboratory Network&nbsp;(JLPPI)&nbsp;echoed&nbsp;the&nbsp;petitioners,&nbsp;saying&nbsp;that&nbsp;the&nbsp;country&nbsp;had&nbsp;insufficient regulations&nbsp;on&nbsp;BPA&nbsp;in&nbsp;food&nbsp;packaging.</p><p>Several countries, such as Austria, Belgium and Canada, have prohibited producers from using BPA in making food contact plastics since 2011.</p><p>In a statement issued in January, the BPOM said studies conducted in the past five years had shown that the migration &mdash; or the transfer of chemical substances from food contact materials into food &mdash; of BPA in the refillable water gallon was under 10 micrograms per kilogram of plastic.</p><p>In&nbsp;2019,&nbsp;the&nbsp;agency&nbsp;issued&nbsp;a&nbsp;regulation&nbsp;limiting&nbsp;the&nbsp;migration&nbsp;of&nbsp;BPA to&nbsp;600&nbsp;micrograms&nbsp;per&nbsp;kg&nbsp;of&nbsp;polycarbonate&nbsp;plastic packaging.</p><p>The BPOM cited several studies from the European Food Safety Authority (EFSA) that highlighted the minimum effect of BPA on humans because data showed that the substance&rsquo;s exposure was too low to affect one&rsquo;s health.</p><p>It also cited information obtained from other studies conducted by international organizations, concluding that the usage of refillable water containers made of polycarbonate does not increase BPA migration levels in water.</p><p><strong>What is the main information of the text?</strong></p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>', 'The local government has successfully supported the clean sanitation for people who live under the bridge.', 'Many poor people don’t have clean water that can support their daily life.', 'Thousa